|||| GENERAL: OVERVIEW

 Let's dip our toes into how this tool works now,

 GST is broken in a chain-like structure,this structure,if we look inside,is made up by 5 parts.
    - Creation
    - Painting
    - Logging and Statistics
    - Rendering

 The creation part is the start of the programm.
 It's main purpose is to figure out if the user wants to use the inputted files as a input or generate their own graph
 either by hand or (soon will be implemented) drawn using a GUI. It's phase doesnt last,but it sets up the foundation
 for the next processes to take place.

 The second part is Painting.
 This is the part in which the programm runs a algorithm on the nodes to paint them based on their statistics and such
 this is the most fun part of the code and it's coded in a way that's made to allow custom-defined functions inside easily.

 Next up we have Logging & Statistics.
 Now this part is mostly for nerds,or to check the details of your graph.
 You can choose so it shows you everything,down to the edge information,weights, etc
 or leave it high level,like only knowing the importance of a node

 Lastly,Rendering.
 This was the most anti-climactic part of the code,as it's only purpose is to
 bundle up the graphs and create seperate windows for them to be shown.
 Although now it has the capability to either run constantly or triggered via event.
 The functionality was added due to the fact that i'll be implementing an A* Algorithm in this tool,
 inorder to determine the shortest path from a node to another node.


